Suppose that, if a randomly chosen bulb produced in the factory is found to be defective, the probability that it was produced by M2 is 2/5. The solubility of barium iodate in an aqueous solution prepared by mixing 200 mL of 0.010 M barium nitrate with 100 mL of 0.10 M sodium iodate is $X \times 10^{-6}$ mol dm. The value of X is ______. 

Use: Solubility product constant ($K_{sp}$) of barium iodate = $1.58 \times 10^{-9}$

text:

At a given temperature, from 10 mg/g and 16 mg/g aqueous phenol solutions, the concentrations of adsorbed phenol are measured to be 4 mg/g and 10 mg/g respectively. At this temperature, the concentration (in mg/g) of adsorbed phenol from 20 mg/g aqueous solution of phenol will be ______. 

Use: $\log_{10} 2 = 0.3$
